Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.93,0:00:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.00,0:00:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers, do you recognize me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.90,0:00:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see this finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it? Can you answer me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.05,0:00:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.71,0:00:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster...is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.95,0:00:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.66,0:00:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster...is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.36,0:00:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming...? What's coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.16,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster...is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.17,0:00:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.44,0:02:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Junkers...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.01,0:02:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're able to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.24,0:02:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the four murders\Nof middle-aged couples
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.75,0:02:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the past two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.45,0:02:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you were seen near the scene\Nof three of them, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.72,0:02:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it, Adolph Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.96,0:03:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind. We know that\Nyou are a lock picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.37,0:03:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Your job is just to open locks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.50,0:03:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Slitting throats\Nin a single stroke...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is not something you could do.\NThat means there were
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.18,0:03:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,other perpetrators\Nin addition to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that there would have to be\Nat least three people
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.62,0:03:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to open a strong lock,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.32,0:03:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and murder a middle-aged couple\Nwithout resistance...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.83,0:03:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost finished\Nmaking a list of men who use knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.53,0:03:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a matter of time\Nbefore we pinpoint your colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.14,0:03:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you talk, or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is not what\NI really want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.01,0:03:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why four couples\Nfrom across Germany...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.35,0:03:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And why only kill\Nmiddle-aged ones without children...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.36,0:04:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Money and items were stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.49,0:04:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but the amounts were too small\Nto split three ways to justify murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.60,0:04:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?\NWant to make a plea bargain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you make a statement,\Nyou can escape prosecution...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.01,0:04:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Who asked you to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers. that's enough.\NThat's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.23,0:04:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to ask you to\Nend this questioning!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, just a little bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.53,0:04:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.90,0:04:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an order from\Nhis attending physician!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.21,0:04:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, all right.\NI'll come again another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will place a guard\Nto watch him closely
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.51,0:04:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he isn't poisoned\Nor that he doesn't disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.58,0:05:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, for some reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.15,0:05:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of trouble\Nseems to happen around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.99,0:05:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.79,0:05:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a joke.\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.41,0:05:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You, where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.18,0:05:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.38,0:05:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing things without permission\Nis going to get me in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even patients need recreation.\NWe're just going out into the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.52,0:05:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're worried,\Ndo you want to come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a warm and pleasant day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.31,0:05:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can talk, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,On days like this,\Nit makes you glad you're alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.75,0:06:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I need days like this,\Nor else it becomes unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I see people in\Nlife and death situations every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.19,0:06:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's easier for doctors to\Nfocus on fame and research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to be like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.40,0:06:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to gain a reputation\Nand do my own research...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.37,0:06:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that succeeding in surgery\Nwas a way to fortify my status...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.48,0:06:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But after performing surgery\Non a certain boy, I changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.28,0:06:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the elder of fraternal twins.\NHe'd been shot in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.09,0:06:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I saved him, I was able to\Nreturn to being a real doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The weight of people's lives\Nare all the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A doctor's work\Nis to save those lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.97,0:07:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.98,0:07:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can start over.\NIt's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.39,0:07:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are close in age,\Nbut you're like my old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.20,0:07:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.77,0:07:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like you're my parent...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.70,0:07:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly have a big kid, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.01,0:07:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was little,\NI wanted a mechanical clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.28,0:07:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind where a nutcracker doll\Nwould stroll out on the hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.52,0:07:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.82,0:07:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I would press my face against\Nthe show window of the watch store...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.53,0:08:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My first break in was that store...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.87,0:08:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They caught me right away\Nand I didn't get the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But, after that,\Nbreak ins became my job...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.74,0:08:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, it was only because\NI wanted that clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.18,0:08:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I only wanted the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.39,0:08:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.99,0:08:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.96,0:08:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the police everything\Nand start over from scratch...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.40,0:08:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My associates, all of them...\NThey were all killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.38,0:08:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Who killed them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.51,0:08:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The one you called "the monster"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.13,0:09:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Make this one yours, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.23,0:09:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through a lot of trouble\Nto set this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.67,0:09:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the daughter of a member of\Nthe state parliament, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.77,0:09:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She is beautiful and intelligent.\NShe's really something...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.34,0:09:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to meet her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.38,0:09:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But...I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.98,0:09:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I should do as you say\Nand settle down...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.88,0:09:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You should!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.88,0:09:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For someone with your prestige\Nto not have a wife... Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.59,0:09:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.69,0:09:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The kind where a nutcracker doll\Nwould pop out every hour...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.50,0:09:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!\NAbout the clock in the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.57,0:09:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's going on?!\NIt's already time for your date! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.32,0:10:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can start over.\NIt's not too late.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.70,0:10:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer... Policeman on watch...\NYou're there, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.51,0:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.95,0:10:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you call Dr. Tenma, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.75,0:10:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.07,0:11:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's late, but can I visit\None of the rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course, Dr. Tenma.\NWhat is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.81,0:11:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I found something good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.13,0:11:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a hold of yourself...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.50,0:11:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.81,0:11:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Candy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.15,0:11:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.83,0:11:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.57,0:12:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the same as the last time...!\NPoisoned by candy!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.61,0:12:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My patient's disappeared...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.61,0:12:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same thing that happened\Nnine years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.68,0:12:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.24,0:12:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.34,0:12:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.34,0:12:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.65,0:12:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't come, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.05,0:12:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to the hospital,\NMr. Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.35,0:12:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything will be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.26,0:12:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't, Doctor. You mustn't come!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.60,0:13:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't see him, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.20,0:13:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"Him?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.57,0:13:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one\Nwho killed my accomplices!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.31,0:13:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be killed, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.22,0:13:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't, Doctor! You mustn't come!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.22,0:13:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time, Doctor.\NIt's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.63,0:13:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago, you saved my life,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.60,0:13:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.14,0:13:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you already forgotten\Nabout those twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.65,0:13:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.85,0:13:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.86,0:14:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, those twins...\NYou remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Run!\NYou'll be killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.57,0:14:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What do you intend to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.57,0:14:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers is my patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.19,0:14:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Execute him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.42,0:14:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.42,0:14:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, run!\NHe killed my friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.53,0:14:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.53,0:14:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We were hired by him!\NHe always called us on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.50,0:14:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A large reward\Nwas transferred into our account
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.43,0:14:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,after each job was done...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd split it between the three of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.94,0:14:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.34,0:14:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who ordered the murders\Nof the four middle-aged couples
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.64,0:14:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.25,0:15:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The police were watching me,\Nso we became a hindrance!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.25,0:15:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already killed Fritz, the Slayer,\Nand Big Boy Boris!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.59,0:15:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before he died, Fritz said,\N"We've been hired by a monster."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.40,0:15:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't think anything of\Nkilling people!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.90,0:15:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Run! Doctor, you'll be killed!\NRun, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.31,0:15:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk too much, Junkers...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.31,0:15:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.68,0:15:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.21,0:15:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers doesn't seem to know\Nwho you are, but I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was your attending physician!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.92,0:15:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You are Johan Liebert, the elder of twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.63,0:15:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the son of Michael Liebert,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.53,0:15:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,former advisor of Commerce\Nin East Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.83,0:15:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,who defected to West Germany\Nin 1936.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:15:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If we know this much about you,\Nyou can't possibly escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.91,0:15:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't add to your crimes, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.74,0:16:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan...?\NI used that name before...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.28,0:16:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is not my real name...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.79,0:16:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My past must not be known...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.89,0:16:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Those four couples\Nand the Lieberts, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.10,0:16:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're different, Doctor...\NYou saved my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.30,0:16:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like my parent, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.41,0:16:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Parent...me...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.98,0:16:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, if it weren't for you,\NI wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.68,0:16:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!\NYou mustn't kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.69,0:16:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why not?"\NWhat do you think a human life is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I saved your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.09,0:16:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to go back to being\Nwhat a doctor should be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.23,0:16:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,By saving your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.60,0:16:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that\Nthe weight of each life is equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has the right to\Ntake another person's life!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.37,0:17:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lived for many years as a doctor\Nwith that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.68,0:17:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.16,0:17:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, after that incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.09,0:17:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you soon became\Nthe Chief of Surgery...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.20,0:17:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad that you were selected\Nas the Chief of Surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.60,0:17:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you want to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.27,0:17:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're here now because
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.41,0:17:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the Director, the Chief of Surgery\Nand the Chief died, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.81,0:17:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really good...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.02,0:17:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be... You did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.39,0:17:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you said it yourself...\NThis is what you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.79,0:18:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When I became conscious,\Nthat's what you said
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.86,0:18:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That you hated them so much\Nyou could kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.37,0:18:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I am not wrong!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.94,0:18:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That bastard... That bastard...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.18,0:18:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's better off dead.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.74,0:18:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,...off dead...off dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.18,0:18:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I did just as you wished, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.19,0:18:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor...I'm afraid, Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.39,0:18:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor... Save me, Doctor...\NI don't want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.50,0:18:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.76,0:19:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was supposed to have died back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.33,0:19:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You brought me back to life, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.27,0:19:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, this rain is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.91,0:19:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate the rain. It washes away\Nall the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.58,0:20:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.09,0:20:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... That means,\Nfrom what you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.20,0:20:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1936, right after the Lieberts\Ndefected from East Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.20,0:20:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with their twin children,\Nthe Liebert family was shot
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.51,0:20:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the parents died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The elder of the twins, the boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.24,0:20:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was hit in the head\Nand in serious condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.25,0:20:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You operated on the boy\Nand saved his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.05,0:20:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But, surprisingly, the boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.22,0:20:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,killed the director, chief of surgery\Nand head of neurosurgery
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.06,0:20:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with poisoned candy and ran away...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.33,0:20:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And last night, he appeared\Nafter nine years
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.37,0:20:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and killed a state police officer,\Nonce again with poisoned candy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.27,0:21:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And shot Adolph Junkers\Nright in front of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.98,0:21:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the one who hired\NJunkers and two others
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.38,0:21:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to kill the four middle-aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.12,0:21:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Johan Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.42,0:21:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's all of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.80,0:21:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.\N-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.70,0:21:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him go for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.04,0:21:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you ever think that someone with\NDr. Tenma's credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.74,0:21:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,would ever commit such a crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.15,0:21:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He has an alibi for the time\Nthe policeman was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.35,0:21:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was no gunpowder residue\Non his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.92,0:21:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, the clue to solving\Nthe murders
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.06,0:21:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the four middle-aged couples\Nis gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.36,0:21:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, shall we\Ngo after the guy, Johan Liebert?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.13,0:21:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge...
